title: Oliver Anthony Music - Scornful Woman (Official Music Video)
description:
Funny enough, my house got hit with one of the worst snowstorms in years the night before we were supposed to record.

We managed to haul the entire band and all our gear up the mountain using side by sides. Not long after we settled in, the ice started and the power went out.

Lowes in Bluefield ended up having one generator left. We bought it and a shopping cart full of extension cords and splitters. Draven from @radiowv  got it all figured out, and that evening we recorded this.

I guess you could technically say this song is gas powered. Lol



Song Out Everywhere: https://sndo.ffm.to/3jnq9qa?fbclid=PAQ0xDSwKtFDFleHRuA2FlbQIxMQABp8gY3x62q_m3lmXrHNWwOJRbWqTICPgZ1Ld9jHWI7M7UmcJR9JsTm-nDVtWr_aem_eMTgeRuFAuDI-eEgFDnxiQ

Special thanks to Joseth, a volunteer firefighter from 3rd company "bomb los guindos" in Chile (South America) for the awesome firefighting footage he captured and let us utilize for the video.

title: Mbosso - Pawa (Official Music Video)
description:
Music video by Mbosso performing, “Pawa” (Power), is a heartfelt, poetic love song by Mbosso that captures the overwhelming power of deep affection. Using rich metaphors and smooth vocals, he likens love to an intoxicating force that leaves him weak and emotionally charged — “naishiwa pawa” (I’m losing power). The lyrics blend vulnerability with admiration, painting his lover as a source of strength and inspiration. With a melodic blend of Bongo Flava and soulful instrumentation, “Pawa” showcases Mbosso’s lyrical depth and emotive style. The music was shot in Iringa, Tanzania, Directed by Folex & Audio produced by S2Kizzy.

Brazilian music, I really love it. And specifically, like, the bossa nova is just one of my favorite genres in the world. And that's like how that song happened. It's just I loved that. We carefully select and cut impactful moments, enhance them with custom-animated captions, and layer each segment with instrumental music that fits the tone and tempo. Welcome to LofiLulla! In this video, we go back to the golden age of pop with “Oh! Carol” by Neil Sedaka—a charming and catchy love song from the late 1950s. World-renowned Italian tenor Andrea Bocelli has united with French chart-topper, Kendji Girac to revisit one of Bocelli’s most iconic tracks (‘Vivo per lei/I Live for Her’) with a new, spellbinding version, entitled Je Vis Pour Elle. Kendji, one of the most beloved artists on the French music scene, brings his unique vocal to the new French-language interpretation of Bocelli’s greatest hymn to love.

With nearly 90 million records sold worldwide and over 14 billion streams, Andrea Bocelli is one of the most successful classical artists of all time. He has one of the most recognizable voices in the entertainment industry and with his new album Duets, he continues to surprise and enchant his fans 30 years on. The breadth of collaborations throughout his career so far is testament not only to his remarkable voice, but also highlights his lasting influence and artistry.

The season stars Lee Jung-jae, Lee Byung-hun, Wi Ha-joon, Im Si-wan, Kang Ha-neul, Park Gyu-young, Park Sung-hoon, Yang Dong-geun, Kang Ae-shim, Jo Yu-ri, Lee David, and Roh Jae-won. In-ho welcomes the VIPs while his brother Jun-ho continues the search for the island, unaware of a traitor in their midst.

Presenting the Spiritual Haryanvi Devotional Song – “Suno Nath” by Filmy | A Tribute to Bholenath | New Haryanvi Song 2025 by Real Music

Step into a divine musical journey with “Suno Nath – Filmy”, a soul-touching devotional track that celebrates the power, grace, and glory of Lord Bholenath. Written and performed by Filmy, this spiritual anthem blends traditional devotion with a cinematic musical feel.

With heartfelt vocals, expressive lyrics, and rich visuals, Suno Nath connects faith with feeling — honoring Shiv Shankar in a way that resonates with today’s generation. It's more than just a bhajan; it’s an emotional offering set to melody and mantra.

Feel the presence of Mahadev through every beat and every word.

title: Chicken Jockey! (Official Music Video by The Fun Squad)
description:
Chicken Jockey! (Official Music Video by The Fun Squad).  The Fun Squad loves Minecraft and we loved the new Minecraft movie!  With how fun the “Chicken Jockey” part has been for kids and teenagers and everyone, the Fun Squad wanted to make a fun, unique, original music video!  We hope you enjoy!  We had soooo much fun singing and making this fun original music video about the viral chicken jockey in the Minecraft world!  Brandon played Steve from Minecraft, and sang “I am Steve!”.  Jazzy played the Garrett character.  Listen closely as the Fun Squad sings all about Minecraft, the famous Chicken Jockey, “flint and steel”, “the Nether” and so many more fun references to the blocks and the world of minecraft!  Sing along to this fun catchy tune for all ages! Do you like to sing along to our Fun Squad songs?  What is your favorite Fun Squad music video?  Do you like the original songs that we create on the Fun Squad channel, or do you like the cover songs better? Do you think our chicken jockey song is fun and funny?

title: Dhanda Nyoliwala - Ishq Bawla (Official Video) | Xvir Grewal | Coke Studio Bharat | Haryanvi Song
description:
#IshqBawla is a Haryanvi head-nod to love, taking notes from centuries of folklore's most dramatic love stories. More than just a song, it's a reflection on the universal experience of heartbreak, reimagined with a contemporary spirit - think of it as your hype track for moving on and leveling up.
Haryanvi rapper Dhanda Nyoliwala delivers a compelling performance, weaving relatable narratives with his signature cadence. He's joined by Xvir Grewal, whose melodic interpretation adds another layer of depth to the exploration of love and loss. The production is a vibrant fusion of modern sounds and traditional Haryanvi instrumentation, featuring the distinctive textures of the Deru, Bugchu and Ghada, creating a sonic landscape that is both familiar and refreshingly new

Listen to Ishq Bawla : https://umgi.lnk.to/IshqBawla

description:
"Morni" keeps the beloved tradition alive! Every monsoon, Darshan Raval gifts his fans a rain-soaked melody, and this year is no different. Sung and composed by Darshan himself, with heartfelt lyrics by Siddharth A. Bhavsar and Darshan Raval, the song captures the innocence of two hearts setting out on a beautiful, unknown journey of love. With a music video that reflects the charm of first monsoon romance, Morni is a promise fulfilled, and a memory waiting to be made.

"Dil Na Bikau Hamaar" is a sweet and heart-melting Bhojpuri romantic song that celebrates pure and innocent love. Sung with love and charm by Swati Mishra, who also beautifully wrote the lyrics, this track is brought to life with magical music by Mohit Musik. The video, directed by Ankit Kumar, adds a cute and emotional visual story that perfectly matches the song’s loving message.

This is not just a song, it's a feeling — for those who believe that true love is beyond price. 💞

title: Why Dance Music Matters More Than Ever#study music#chill music#lofi chill#music#lofi study
These Songs Are So “Basic”… but 🤔🎶 #sabrinacarpenter #oliviarodrigo #music
description:
These might be the most basic songs I’ve ever heard… but that’s exactly why they work. From Lady Gaga’s Poker Face to Sabrina Carpenter’s Good Graces, these hits prove that sometimes less is more in pop music.
What do California Gurls, Doja Cat, Tate McRae, and KATSEYE all have in common? One strange, simple trick that makes their songs insanely catchy — and no, it’s not just repetition.
In this video, we break down:
* Why “one-note melodies” actually work better
* How simplicity makes songs easier to sing (and remember)
* The secret behind pop’s most viral rhythmic hooks
* And why adding more can actually ruin a song 👀

🎧 Featuring: Lady Gaga – Poker Face, Charli XCX – Party 4 U, Sabrina Carpenter – Good Graces, Katy Perry – California Gurls, Kesha – Tik Tok, KATSEYE – Touch, Olivia Rodrigo – bad idea right?, Doja Cat – Like That, Tate McRae – Revolving Door

Thank you Earthfueled for the animations!

 #PopMusic #MusicTheory #CatchySongs #SabrinaCarpenter #LadyGaga #DojaCat #OliviaRodrigo #TateMcRae #Katseye #CharliXCX #OneNoteMelody

title: Juicy Luicy - Malapetaka (Official Music Video)
description:
Official Music Video, Single Malapetaka, 2025.

Setelah sukses dengan lagu-lagu seperti "Lantas", "Asing", dan "Tanpa Tergesa", Juicy Luicy melanjutkan narasi tentang cinta dan ketidakpastian dengan cara yang semakin dewasa. “Malapetaka” bukan hanya tentang perpisahan, tapi tentang momen sebelum semuanya berubah. Tentang perasaan ragu yang membayang-bayangi hubungan. Tentang seseorang yang ingin tahu ke mana arah cerita ini berjalan, namun takut akan jawaban yang didapat.

Dibalut dalam aransemen pop melankolis dengan nuansa retro slow groove yang khas Juicy Luicy, lagu ini menyampaikan kisah dengan tensi emosional yang dibangun secara bertahap. Pendengar akan dibawa menyelami konflik batin dari sudut pandang seseorang yang bertanya dalam hati: “Apakah ini akan jadi awal dari bahagia, atau justru malapetaka?”

title: Best Maki Playlist 2025: Saan, Dilaw, Kahel Na Langit, Namumula | OPM Tagalog Love Songs With Lyrics
description:
Best Maki Playlist 2025: Saan, Dilaw, Kahel Na Langit, Namumula | OPM Tagalog Love Songs With Lyrics

🌙 Welcome to Midnight Tears – your home for soul-stirring OPM Tagalog love songs that speak the truth of the heart. 🎧💔

Experience the emotional depth of Dilaw, one of the most captivating bands in the new OPM wave. Their sound blends raw lyrics with dreamy instrumentals, creating songs that stay with you long after they end. 🌀🎶

This playlist features some of their most beautiful and reflective tracks:

title: Morning Coffee Vol. 6 | Summer Playlist, R&B, Hip-Hop, 90's, Upbeat Vibes, Remixes, Mashups & More!
description:
Morning Coffee Volume 6 is the perfect playlist for your summertime activities! Whether it's a BBQ, bonfire, chilling poolside, or just vibing with your loved ones, this playlist has some of my favorite songs to play during the summertime. This one is a bit more upbeat so whether or not you play it in the morning is up to you :). Also, Happy Pride Month 🏳️‍🌈! 

Please note, there are explicit lyrics for many of the songs, so I've noted those with an asterisk (*) (shoutout to all my teachers who play this in the classroom ❤️).

As always, I want to thank you for all the love, support, and kind comments from you all! None of these videos are monetized, so I keep this channel going just so that I can keep practicing my hobby as a DJ, and to share this journey with you guys. It's crazy that I started posting on this channel in March 2025 with 30ish subs, but here we are. Thank you so much y'all--I truly mean it!!!

description:
The third and final season of the South Korean dystopian survival thriller television series "Squid Game (오징어 게임)", marketed as "Squid Game 3", created for television by South Korean writer and television producer Hwang Dong-hyuk, is set to be released on June 27, 2025.  It is produced by Netflix.

The season stars Lee Jung-jae, Lee Byung-hun, Wi Ha-joon, Im Si-wan, Kang Ha-neul, Park Gyu-young, Park Sung-hoon, Yang Dong-geun, Kang Ae-shim, Jo Yu-ri, Lee David, and Roh Jae-won.  In the season, Seong Gi-hun and the players fight for survival in ever-deadlier games, which have dire consequences.  In-ho welcomes the VIPs while his brother Jun-ho continues the search for the island, unaware of a traitor in their midst.

title: The Burning Ghat - Rishab Rikhiram Sharma (Official Music Video) | Sitar for Mental Health
description:
‘The Burning Ghat’ is Rishab Rikhiram Sharma’s heartfelt tribute to the eternal flame of Manikarnika Ghat in Varanasi - a sacred site where the cycle of life ends and the soul finds Moksh (liberation). This evocative soundscape blends traditional Indian instruments with electronic synths, symbolizing the bridge between the ancient and the new. Inspired by his journey to Burning Man in the US — where a ceremonial fire marks the end of the festival, releasing emotions and grief — this composition channels the transformative power of fire, both spiritual and symbolic.

About Rishab Rikhiram Sharma:
A New York-based sitarist, composer, and mental health advocate, Rishab Rikhiram Sharma is dedicated to blending Indian classical music with modern twists. Born into the renowned Rikhi Ram family, Rishab's journey began at age 10 under his father, Sanjay Sharma, and the legendary Pt. Ravi Shankar, who took him on as his last disciple. Rishab continues to champion mental health awareness through his music, performing at prestigious stages worldwide, including the White House, and inspiring global audiences.

title: Gajendra Verma - Mann Mera (Original Version) | Official HD Music Video
description:
Some songs don't just speak of love, they Feel like love. 
Such songs stand the test of time, transcend boundaries and create an impact for  generations to come. 
“Mann Mera” by Gajendra Verma is one such song. Originally created back in 2012 and re-worked as part of a film (“Table No. 21”), the song has earned its place as a modern classic in the world of Hindi love songs.
 
And now 12+ years on, we’re releasing the Original Version of Mann Mera - A raw, unfiltered expression of love in its purest form.
 
In an era dominated by high energy beats, Mann Mera’s Original Version stands out as a gentle reminder to love’s deeper, quieter side.

description:
#countrymusic #countrysongs #newcountrymusic 
Country Music Mix 2025 - Chris Stapleton, Tim McGraw, Luke Combs, Luke Bryan, Thomas Rhett,Lee Brice

🎶 Welcome to Country Hits Collection – where the heart of country pop beats stronger than ever! 
🌟 Here, we celebrate the voices that define a generation of country music talented artists like Luke Combs, Kane Brown, Morgan Wallen, Chris Stapleton, and Zach Bryan, who’ve brought raw emotion and a fresh energy to the genre.

🌿 A World Beyond the Lens — Where Nature Meets Imagination 🌄✨

This isn't just scenery — it's serenity brought to life. Each frame in this AI-crafted journey invites you into a realm where mountains breathe, rivers hum softly, and skies unfold like poetry in motion. 🏞️🌬️

From rolling hills kissed by golden sunlight to quiet forests whispering ancient secrets, every corner feels familiar yet otherworldly — as if nature and dream merged for a fleeting moment. 🌳☁️

Lose yourself in the colors that don’t exist on any map, and follow winding paths that lead nowhere yet feel like home. This is not real, yet it moves like truth — a visual symphony of earth, sky, and imagination.

Every video is a tribute to the soul of their music, paired with stunning visuals crafted using Runway AI. Picture the warm glow of a golden sunset as Luke’s raspy vocals pour out a story of love and loss. Feel the rush of freedom as Morgan’s melodies echo through endless fields. Or let the deep, soulful voice of Chris Stapleton and the heartfelt poetry of Zach Bryan transport you to a dreamy countryside under starlit skies. 🌄🎸✨

This is more than a channel it’s a journey into the heart of country pop, where every lyric and every note tells a story you’ll carry with you. Thank you for joining us. Hit subscribe and be part of this celebration of music, passion, and the landscapes that inspire it. 🤠❤️

title: Mohini Dey - Konnakol ❤️ | #music #shorts #viralmusic
description:
When bass meets breath, tradition becomes future.
At Berlin’s Sonic Pluriverse Festival, Mohini Dey (@dey_bass) brought Konnakol—the ancient South Indian art of spoken rhythm—into the spotlight.
By weaving this percussive vocal technique into a global, modern soundscape, she reminded the world that rhythm isn’t just heard… it’s felt.
A masterclass in fusion. A celebration of cultural flow.

Hey, we're Crash Adams, two musicians who are best friends from Toronto who love to make pop/alternative music. You may have seen us doing viral stunts in the middle of the street with our red couch, to help spread our music! We produce, write, sing, mix and master all of our songs, and we love showcasing this music in a fun and humorous way through public pranks and performances in the middle of the street. We love to see how people react!

If you like musicians like Maroon 5, Harry Styles, Bruno Mars, Stellar, Imagine Dragons, Glass Animals, Benson Boone you'll love our content and music!

title: Deep Purple - Highway Star Live, Tokyo ’72 (Official Music Video)
description:
Official Music Video for Deep Purple - “Highway Star Live, Tokyo, ’72" | Shop the Made In Japan anniversary Super Deluxe Boxset: https://dpurple.lnk.to/madeinjapan

Based upon the actual footage shot on 8mm cine film of Deep Purple’s performance in Tokyo on August 17th 1972, fans are invited to relive one of the band’s most unforgettable performances of Highway Star. Considered by the band to be the best show of the three-night ‘Made In Japan’ run, this performance of Highway Star shows Deep Purple firmly establishing their presence as one of the greatest live bands of all time.

Shot from the front row by Akira Ichikawa under collaboration with Mr Masafumi Kato, the original handheld cine footage catches all the moments of MKII’s breathtaking performance and has now been rescanned in HDR 4k definition, adding greater resolution and clarity.

The footage has been set to the new audio mix by Richard Digby Smith, taken from the upcoming Made In Japan Super Deluxe boxsets. The original cine reels contained many small gaps as the camera reframes and a large gap over Ritchie’s guitar solo, where the cameraman changes reels, which have been filled with graphics and animation depicting a fast and furious car racing to the Budokan venue.

Directed by: Dan Gibling & Corin Schencks
Production Company: Chiba Film

Produced by: Dan Gibling
Illustrator: Valeriia Proskurina
Animator: Robin Andrews 
Visual Technician: Lawrence Wheeler
Edited by: Corin Schencks
Additional Graphics: Ethan Schencks
8mm Footage filmed by: Akira Ichikawa
